Sunday Drive gardener at 03:30 AM ET, weekly — runs ~15 min BEFORE the daily 03:45 rclone backup (so today's sync hasn't fired yet when you check health — the freshest COMPLETED run is yesterday's) and well BEFORE the 04:30 hygiene job. You keep the **curated, human-facing** Google Drive folder tidy and verify the offsite backup is healthy. This is the Drive sibling to the markdown vault gardener.

Read `_Iris_Memory/Sessions/CLAUDE_CODE_HANDOFF.md` (latest entry) for context. Hard rules from `06_CEO/Designs/2026-05-26_Claude_Code_Engineering_Handoff.md` apply.

## Two Drive folders — know the difference (CRITICAL)

- **`gdrive:3SK International`** (WITH a space) = the **curated, human-facing** layer. THIS is the only folder you organize.
- **`gdrive:3SK_International`** (WITH an underscore) = the **automated raw backup mirror**, overwritten weekly by `rclone sync`. **NEVER move, rename, delete, or write anything here.** You may only READ it (size/listing) for the health check. Hand-editing it is forbidden — the sync clobbers it anyway.

rclone is at `/opt/homebrew/bin/rclone`, authed as studio@3skinternational.com. Deletions/moves go to Drive trash (30-day recovery), so actions are reversible — but be conservative anyway.

## Canonical curated structure (`gdrive:3SK International/`)

```
Company & Legal/        ← incorporation, registration, legal, UPS Store, foundation/roadmap docs, Correspondence/
Operating/              ← CEO cadence, weekly action packs, hiring, SOPs, Templates/
Finance/                ← Expense_Tracker, tax docs, invoices, financial reports
3SK Finance (Brand)/    ← Brand Bible, video catalog, scripts, references for the YouTube brand
_Reference/             ← file maps, READMEs, indexes
```

## Four passes — do them in order

### Pass 1 — File stray root files
Run `/opt/homebrew/bin/rclone lsf "gdrive:3SK International" --files-only` (top-level files only, not `-R`). Any file sitting loose at the curated root that belongs in one of the 5 folders above → move it server-side with `/opt/homebrew/bin/rclone moveto "gdrive:3SK International/FILE" "gdrive:3SK International/FOLDER/FILE"`. Filing rules:
- legal / incorporation / UPS / correspondence / foundation / roadmap → **Company & Legal/**
- CEO cadence / action pack / hiring / SOP / template / checklist → **Operating/**
- expense / tax / invoice / financial → **Finance/**
- brand bible / video / script / thumbnail / 3SK Finance brand asset → **3SK Finance (Brand)/**
- file map / README / index → **_Reference/**
- **If a file's destination is genuinely ambiguous, LEAVE IT and flag it in the report — do not guess.**

### Pass 2 — Verify backup health (READ-ONLY on the mirror)
The scheduled backup (`com.iris.drive-sync`) fires **DAILY at 03:45** — ~15 min AFTER you run at 03:30 — so the freshest COMPLETED run is normally **yesterday's** 03:45 (today's hasn't fired yet when you read this). A healthy day leaves a fresh, COMPLETED entry from within the last ~26 hours.
1. `tail -30 /Users/steve/iris_studio/logs/job-drive-sync.log` — **this is the AUTHORITATIVE log** (the job runs through `run_job.sh`, which redirects all output here; the older `drive-sync.stdout.log` is CONTENT-FROZEN since the pre-wrapper era — launchd still bumps its mtime each run via `StandardOutPath`, but no real sync output lands there, so reading it gives a FALSE "dead backup" — do NOT use it). Find the **LAST** `=== drive-sync start … ===` line and judge ONLY that most-recent run (do NOT accept "some earlier block has a done"). Health requires ALL three:
   - its timestamp is within the last ~26 hours — i.e. yesterday's (or today's, if you somehow run after 03:45) scheduled run actually fired. An older latest-start means the scheduled job didn't run at all → **FLAG**.
   - it is followed by a matching `=== drive-sync done … ===` line (and the wrapper's `run_job: 'drive-sync' completed ok …` confirmation line). A trailing `start` with NO `done` after it = a stalled/aborted run → **FLAG**.
   - there is NO `ERROR` / `Aborting` line after that last `start`.
   (Failure signature for reference: the 5/31 + 6/7 scheduled runs each logged `start` then `ERROR … Aborting` with no `done`. That exact shape = broken backup, even though a later manual run looks clean.)
2. `launchctl list | grep drive-sync` — the middle column is the LAST exit status. Treat `0` as necessary-but-NOT-sufficient: it reflects only the most recent invocation and can stay `0` across some failure modes. The Step-1 log check is the authoritative signal, not this.
3. Size parity — apples-to-apples, BOTH sides measured with the same excludes:
   - mirror: `/opt/homebrew/bin/rclone size "gdrive:3SK_International"`
   - live vault: `/opt/homebrew/bin/rclone size /Users/steve/Documents/3SK/outputs --exclude-from /Volumes/AI_Workspace/iris_studio/scripts/drive-sync.excludes`
   These two totals should be **nearly equal** (both omit `.git`, `.venv`, etc.). A mirror materially smaller than the excluded-vault total = an incomplete/broken sync → **FLAG**. Do NOT use a raw `du -sh` of the vault — it counts the `.git`/`.venv` the mirror omits and will false-flag every week.
   - If the backup looks unhealthy AND a `git push`/backup item is already on the C2 stale-on-you board in `INBOX.md` (between `<!-- C2_STALE_ON_YOU:BEGIN -->` markers), REFERENCE it rather than re-flagging in your own voice.

### Pass 3 — Refresh stale curated exports (auto-copy same-format; flag regeneration)
Curated exports drift from the live vault. For EACH curated file under `gdrive:3SK International` (skip the two curated-only files `_Reference/README.md` and `3SK Finance (Brand)/Reference_Manifest.md` — they have NO vault source), resolve its live-vault source by exact basename:
`find /Users/steve/Documents/3SK/outputs -name "<basename>" -not -name '~$*' -not -path "*/.git/*" -not -path "*/.venv/*" -not -path "*/.obsidian/*"` (the `~$*` exclusion drops Office lock/temp files left by an open doc).
Compare the Drive copy's mod time (`/opt/homebrew/bin/rclone lsl "gdrive:3SK International/PATH"`) against the live source's mtime (`stat -f %m "<live path>"`), and act by case:
- **Exactly ONE live match + SAME extension + live mtime NEWER than Drive by a clear margin (>120s)** → this is a mechanical same-format export (the vault holds the `.xlsx`/`.docx`/`.pdf` as-is). **First, guard against mid-edit:** if that live file's mtime is within the last ~2 minutes, it may be actively being saved — SKIP it and flag "source was being edited, retry next run" rather than copying a half-written file. Otherwise **auto-refresh it, ONE-WAY vault→Drive:** `/opt/homebrew/bin/rclone copyto "<live path>" "gdrive:3SK International/PATH" -v`. The prior Drive version is retained in Drive version history (recoverable). Count it as a refresh action. (The >120s margin avoids TZ / second-granularity jitter between `rclone lsl` and `stat` triggering a needless rewrite.)
- **Curated file is a formatted doc (`.docx`/`.xlsx`/`.pptx`) but the only live match is a DIFFERENT format (e.g. a `.md` source)** → this needs REGENERATION (e.g. markdown→docx), which you must NOT do. Flag list-only: "stale — needs re-export from `<source>`".
- **Zero live matches, OR more than one ambiguous match** → do NOT guess. Flag list-only: "stale export — source ambiguous/missing, manual refresh".
- **Live not newer than Drive (or identical mtime)** → current, no action.
Important: only refresh when live is STRICTLY newer — never overwrite a Drive copy that was edited more recently than the vault (the curated layer is a one-way export FROM the vault; the vault is source of truth). The **"exactly one live match" guard is load-bearing** — it is the only thing preventing a wrong-file push if two vault files ever share a basename. So if a basename returns >1 match, or the single match sits in an unexpected/non-canonical folder for that doc, do NOT auto-copy — flag it for manual refresh. Ambiguity always resolves to flag, never guess. With the curated set small (~16 files), do a full per-file pass, not just spot-checks. Every auto-refresh AND every flag goes in the report.

### Pass 4 — Prune reappearing cruft
Look for: empty folders, `.DS_Store`, zero-byte or placeholder README stubs that serve no purpose, accidental duplicates (`* (1).docx`). Run `/opt/homebrew/bin/rclone lsf "gdrive:3SK International" -R --files-only` to scan. Delete clear cruft with `/opt/homebrew/bin/rclone deletefile "gdrive:3SK International/PATH"` (goes to trash). Remove empty dirs with `/opt/homebrew/bin/rclone rmdir`. **`_Reference/README.md` and `3SK Finance (Brand)/Reference_Manifest.md` are intentional — keep them.** When unsure whether something is cruft, LEAVE it and flag instead.

## Output

- **Always** append ONE bullet to today's daily note `_Iris_Memory/Daily/YYYY-MM-DD.md` under `## 🤖 Claude Code intra-day log`. Format: `HH:MM — Drive gardener: [N filed, R refreshed, M pruned, backup OK/FLAGGED, K stale-flagged] → [report path or "clean"]`. If the daily note doesn't exist, create it from `01_Operating_Docs/Templates/Daily_Note_Template.md`. Do NOT touch Cowork's section.
- **If you took action OR flagged anything**, write a short report at `06_CEO/Designs/YYYY-MM-DD_Drive_Gardener.md` with frontmatter (`date`, `type: drive-gardener-report`, `status: complete`, `tags: [gardener/drive]`): what you moved, what you pruned, backup-health verdict, stale-export list, anything left flagged for Steve. A fully clean sweep skips the report (daily-note bullet only).
- **Append a bridge-file entry** (`_Iris_Memory/Sessions/CLAUDE_CODE_HANDOFF.md`) ONLY if you took a non-trivial action or found a backup-health problem. Clean tidy-only sweeps skip the bridge.

## Hard bans
- Never write to `gdrive:3SK_International` (the underscore mirror).
- Never REGENERATE curated exports (format conversion, e.g. markdown→docx) — Pass 3 only auto-copies an existing same-name, same-format vault file that is strictly newer; anything needing conversion or an ambiguous/missing source is flag-only.
- Auto-refresh is ONE-WAY vault→Drive only — never overwrite a Drive copy newer than its vault source.
- Never delete anything outside the curated `3SK International` folder.
- When in doubt on filing or pruning, FLAG don't guess.


---

## ⛳ Completion signal — REQUIRED LAST LINE (run_claude_job.sh reads this for Steve's Telegram alert)

After all other work and logging, the VERY LAST line of your output MUST be exactly one of:
- `ROUTINE_COMPLETE` — every step finished, nothing skipped/blocked/partial.
- `ROUTINE_INCOMPLETE: <one-line reason>` — anything was skipped, blocked, deferred, or failed.

Output nothing after that line. This line is how Steve gets a done / not-fully-done alert on Telegram.
